S. Africa Finds No Trace of Foot and Mouth in Gauteng, Sapa Says

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-03-28T14:55:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/s-africa-finds-no-trace-of-foot-and-mouth-in-gauteng-sapa-says.html
South Africa  found no trace of foot
and mouth disease at a feedlot belonging to Karan Beef in
Heidelberg, in the country’s Gauteng province, the South African
Press Association said, citing the company’s veterinarian Dirk
Verwoerd.  The beef supplier had placed its its feedlot in Heidelberg
under quarantine as a precaution on March 18 following a recent
outbreak of the disease in the Ingwavuma area in KwaZulu-Natal,
the news agency said. Some cattle from that area had been
transported to the feedlot.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg bureau   mmancotywa1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net . 